added.title: The Streak Part 1
added.description: It's Crime Season and Robin is determined to continue his streak of stopping 52 crimes every year.

added.title: The Streak Part 2
added.description: Robin's streak of stopping 52 crimes every year is in jeopardy when members of his team are poached by Kid Flash.

added.title: Two Parter Part 1
added.description: The Titans visit the Hall of Justice to use the pool, but then decide to check out the inside.

added.title: The Misunderstandings
added.description: Gumball has misunderstood about his date with Penny. He thought they were meeting for dinner but they were actually meeting for lunch at a Diner called Dinner. He runs to the mall but everyone he meets on the way seems to misunderstand him in a different way. Once he finally does get to the mall, it seems all his misunderstandings have caught up with him.

added.title: The Blame
added.description: Gumball gives Billy his first taste of videogames but the sheer excitement causes him to pass out. His mother Felicity summons the PTA and threatens to ban video games all across Elmore. Gumball and Darwin are given three chances to prove that videogames can be a force for good. But when they fail, they decide to prove books can be just as dangerous.

added.title: The Detective
added.description: Anais arrives in the bedroom to find a messy crime-scene and her Daisy doll missing. She realizes Gumball and Darwin are the chief suspects. Following a series of clues is her only chance to track them down and her only hope of learning what happened to Daisy. But as the mystery unravels, it seems the culprits may have turned on each other.

added.title: The Compilation
added.description: A compilation of some of the funniest, most bizarre clips uploaded onto the internet by the people of Elmore. Clips include Banana Joe's self-choreographed acrobatics, Richard's latest culinary invention and Gumball and Darwin's contest for who can pull the weirdest face.

added.title: The Disaster
added.description: When Rob purchases a universal remote from the Awesome Store, he discovers can control the entire universe. He rewinds into the past and remembers Gumball had left him in The Void, leaving him scarred and in his current mutated shape. He uses the universal remote to destroy Gumball's life, whilst Gumball has to figure out what's going on before he's ejected once and for all.

added.title: How I Like My Food Music Video
added.description: Richard's food ballad.

added.title: The Small Hours Music Video
added.description: Compilation of Mr. Small's singles.

added.title: Filth Everywhere Music Video
added.description: Teri's playful J-pop song.

added.title: Singing Music Video
added.description: Join the citizens of Elmore for a song and dance spectacular.

added.title: Billy Pharham in Your House Music Video
added.description: The Billy Pharham rap.

added.title: Hairy Lady Music Video
added.description: Principal Brown serenades Miss Simian with a reluctant cameo from Larry.

added.title: Banana Song Music Video
added.description: Banana fails dramatically.

added.title: Pluto's Lament Music Video
added.description: Pluto feels left out.

added.title: The People's Song Music Video
added.description: Secondary characters take the lead in this musical number.

added.title: Gumball: Elmore News 2
added.description: From a high-speed police chase to the inside scoop on Daisy the Donkey, Channel 6 Elmore News has all the top hard-hitting local stories. Experienced newscaster Kip Schlezinger is the man to bring you the latest news, sports and weather, even when there is absolutely nothing to report.

added.title: Gumball: Elmore News 4
added.description: From a high-speed police chase to the inside scoop on Daisy the Donkey, Channel 6 Elmore News has all the top hard-hitting local stories. Experienced newscaster Kip Schlezinger is the man to bring you the latest news, sports and weather, even when there is absolutely nothing to report.

added.title: Gumball: Elmore News 5
added.description: From a high-speed police chase to the inside scoop on Daisy the Donkey, Channel 6 Elmore News has all the top hard-hitting local stories. Experienced newscaster Kip Schlezinger is the man to bring you the latest news, sports and weather, even when there is absolutely nothing to report.

added.title: Gumball: Elmore News 1
added.description: From a high-speed police chase to the inside scoop on Daisy the Donkey, Channel 6 Elmore News has all the top hard-hitting local stories. Experienced newscaster Kip Schlezinger is the man to bring you the latest news, sports and weather, even when there is absolutely nothing to report.

added.title: Gumball: Elmore News 3
added.description: From a high-speed police chase to the inside scoop on Daisy the Donkey, Channel 6 Elmore News has all the top hard-hitting local stories. Experienced newscaster Kip Schlezinger is the man to bring you the latest news, sports and weather, even when there is absolutely nothing to report.

added.title: Craig World
added.description: Craig creates an amusement park in the Creek! But when things start to get stale, he vows to make it bigger and better, no matter what it takes!

added.title: Body Swap
added.description: Fed up with their home experiences, Craig, Kelsey and JP agree to switch bodies!

added.title: Copycat Carter
added.description: Craig and his friends stumble upon Carter, the cardboard genius turned cyborg, and Craig decides to help Carter become a kid again, just like him!

added.title: Brother Builder
added.description: As Craig races against time to build a super important invention, we learn how Craig became such a clever inventor!

added.title: Simons Are Forever
added.description: Duncan and Leshawna try to take advantage of Izzy's love for the game of Simon Says.

added.title: Stop! Hamster Time
added.description: Owen takes over the job of caring for the class hamster and learns that he's evil.

added.title: Driving Miss Crazy
added.description: Duncan leads Beth to believe she's broken his battery-powered bike and makes her chauffeur him around in a wagon for the day as punishment.

added.title: Charlene Mania
added.description: When Vic attempts to have the perfect day off, the town's sudden obsession for Charlene gets in his way.

added.title: Old Man Teo
added.description: When Vic and Val are tasked to volunteer at an Old Folks' Home, Val becomes buddies with the oldest, crankiest person in Monte Macabre and helps him reclaim his youthful power.

added.title: Poacher Patrol
added.description: When Don bestows Val the responsibility of patrolling the lake, Val takes it too far and stops who he believes to be a poacher -- with disastrous consequences.

added.title: The Eater
added.description: It's Halloween and Apple's not feeling quite right. He takes Onion into the dark depths to find out why.

added.title: Apple & Onion's Booth
added.description: Apple and Onion must save their favorite booth at Pizza's Diner from a Texas oil tycoon.

added.title: Ferekh
added.description: Apple and Onion are put in charge of Falafel's beloved rooster but it turns out that other parties have a vested interest in it too.

added.title: Reststop Roustabout
added.description: With the Rustbucket stopped on the Midwest roadside, Ben locks himself inside with his tablet as Max and Gwen enjoy the great outdoors, until Team Tennyson is pulled into a wild Jack-a-Lope chase.

added.title: That's the Stuff
added.description: While touring a space museum, Ben's excitement multiplies when he learns that recently discovered space stuff is being examined inside the museum's lab. Once the stuff comes to life and the shape-shifting goo replicates our hero, Ben must look within if he is to stop the case of mistaken identity.

added.title: The Feels
added.description: While Max and Gwen revel in the holiday spirit of Winter Wonderland, Ben couldn't be more unamused and focused on the toys, but once the Weatherheads set their sights on Winter Wonderland as their next target, our hero must become one with his emotion if he is to save the town.

added.title: Past Aliens Present
added.description: After Ben stumbles upon a video of Cannonbolt ripping up a computer lab on the internet, Team Tennyson must race to State U to find the imposter; but once Ben discovers it is a steam-punk version of his alien that is terrorizing the campus, Ben must take down the man behind the machine, Steam Smythe!

added.title: Dreamtime
added.description: After a series of reoccurring nightmares affect his sleep, Ben refuses to open up to Max and Gwen about what's bothering him, but once they realize Zombozo himself is behind it, Ben must accept Max and Gwen's help if they are going to put a stop to the terror.

added.title: Wednesday - Part 3
added.description: Elliott and his mom Frankie are about to have a Wednesday they'll never forget, when a mysterious rock unexpectedly transports them somewhere across the universe. Finding themselves in a strange new environment with strange new creatures, they meet a dinosaur named Mo - and that's just the beginning of their out of this world adventure!

added.title: Wednesday - Part 4
added.description: Elliott and his mom Frankie are about to have a Wednesday they'll never forget, when a mysterious rock unexpectedly transports them somewhere across the universe. Finding themselves in a strange new environment with strange new creatures, they meet a dinosaur named Mo - and that's just the beginning of their out of this world adventure!

added.title: #GothamCon
added.description: A fun day for Barbara Gordon and her bestie Harleen Quinzel (at Gotham City's annual geekfest, the Annual Convention of Gotham City Enthusiats!) is turned on its head when, out of nowhere, the villainous Harley Quinn shows up to wreak havoc! Lucky for everyone, Batgirl just happens to be in the area...

added.title: #SoulSisters Part 1
added.description: The girls must track down Katana, a mysterious warrior who's stealing the souls of Metropolis's villains. Meanwhile, Diana's new friend Tatsu is a perfect match for her in every way, but may have a connection to Katana.

added.title: #SoulSisters Part 2
added.description: The girls must track down Katana, a mysterious warrior who's stealing the souls of Metropolis's villains. Meanwhile, Diana's new friend Tatsu is a perfect match for her in every way, but may have a connection to Katana.

added.title: #Abracadabrapalooza
added.description: In an attempt to make Karen feel better about a pimple, Zee recounts her embarrassing transition into magichood, and the rift it created between her and her father.

added.title: #RageCat
added.description: Jessica Cruz is convinced she can find the purr-fect forever home for Dexter, a cat who has been deemed unadoptable because he's basically the worst cat in the world. Her overbearing persistence in trying to get him adopted leads Dexter to become Dex-Starr, an evil Red Lantern supervillain! Can Jess still find the good in a fuzzy little nemesis who is trying to kill her?

added.title: #TheGoodTheBadAndTheBizarre
added.description: Everything is going well for Kara Danvers, both as a teen and a superhero, until she starts taking the blame for things she didn't do, and the emergence of a new supervillain threatens to destroy Supergirl's hard-earned reputation.

added.title: #BackInAFlash
added.description: After an embarrassing incident ruins Barbara Gordon's reputation, rather than owning it and moving on, she decides it's easier to harness The Flash's newly discovered ability to travel back in time and alter the delicate fabric of the space-time continuum.

added.title: Ranger Tabes
added.description: To recover a missing package, the Bears get help from Ranger Tabes, an eccentric forest ranger. But her overblown sense of justice might be too much for the Bears to handle.

added.title: Rooms
added.description: The Bears switch bedrooms for the night and get a glimpse of the living space of one of their brothers. But the deeper they go, hidden secrets are revealed.

added.title: Losing Ice
added.description: Feeling unappreciated, Ice Bear leaves his brothers to be the chef of a restaurant. Desperate to fill the void, Grizz and Panda look for Ice Bear's replacement.

added.title: Cellie
added.description: Fed up with sharing, Panda forbids his brothers from using his cellphone any longer. But when the brothers get their own super advanced smartphones, Panda starts to succumb to crippling jealousy.

added.title: Fashion Bears
added.description: In order to abide by the clothing policy of their favorite Boba shop, the Bears get some new outfits. But with new looks come new lives including office work, fashion modeling and even falling in love!

added.title: What About Cool James?
added.description: Seth wants some attention, but his family's too busy. But when a lucky explosion forces Cool James to stay with him, Seth gets the attention he craves! That is until Seth sees how much his family loves Cool James.

added.title: Dino Club
added.description: Pressured to choose a real job, Seth instead decides to be a dinosaur like Pam! Soon, all the kids follow suit, but cause so much trouble, Fungietown bans dinosaurs! But Pam can't stop being a dinosaur and is thrown in jail!

added.title: Gem Drill
added.description: Steven takes a journey deep underground.

added.title: Same Old World
added.description: Steven flies around the world.

added.title: Barn Mates
added.description: Steven helps two friends get along at the barn.

added.title: Hit the Diamond
added.description: Steven and the Gems play an old fashioned game of baseball.

added.title: Steven Floats
added.description: Steven is so excited to be back home that he jumps for joy and jumps way too high.

added.title: Adopt a Jackal
added.description: After a battle with the Mutants, Jackalman gets confused and accidentally returns to the Cats' Lair with the Thundercats, he is the dumbest mutant. Jackalman pretends to be a Thundercat so his enemies won't catch him and the Thundercats pretend to play along because they feel bad for him!

added.title: Summer Fun Day!
added.description: The Thundercats are exhausted from fighting bad guys all the time so Lion-O suggests they spend a relaxing summer fun day at the beach, with no fighting! Unfortunately the beach is home to the Crabmen, giant, clawed humanoids that fight anyone who steps on their sand! Looks like summer fun day might involve some fighting!

added.title: Safari Joe
added.description: While minding her own business, Cheetara is caught in a trap set by Safari Joe, the famously annoying hunter! After escaping, she rallies the other ThunderCats to help her stop Joe once and for all, by turning the tables and capturing him!

added.title: Ratar-O
added.description: The ThunderCats have gotten so good at defeating the Mutants of Plun-Darr that it's basically become routine. That all changes with the arrival of the Mutants' old leader: Ratar-O, wielder of the Sword of Plun-Darr! Uh-oh!

added.title: Prince Starling's Quest
added.description: Lion-O is happily playing with Snarf in their "Frolicking Field" and doesn't have a care in the world, unfortunately he's accidentally stomping all over the miniature village of the Micrits! The tiny people want to defeat the "giant orange monster" but such a quest would require a brave hero. Luckily, the Micrits have such a hero: Prince Starling! Now, let us the tell you the epic tale of Prince Starling as he journeys to find the fountain of growth and defeat the wicked Lion-O, who has no idea any of this is going on!

added.title: Dungeon Crawl!
added.description: Having joined forces with the Lowly in their quest to defeat King Vangelis, Cole, Wu, and Vania have to find a way out of the bottom of the mountain, a place said to be inescapable.

added.title: Grief Bringer
added.description: Nya and Kai, who have become the respective leaders of the Munce and Geckles, attempt to unite the tribes in an effort to defeat their mutual enemy, the Skull Sorcerer, who schemes against them.

added.title: Masters Never Quit
added.description: Pursued by a magma monster, Cole, Princess Vania, Wu & the Lowly arrive at a mysterious temple deep in Shintaro Mountain, a temple which was once a training ground for Earth Elementals including Cole's own mother, Lilly!

added.title: The Darkest Hour
added.description: Forced to flee by the arrival of Grief-Bringer, the ninja, the Munce and the Geckles take refuge in the Geckle Strong-Cave. But the bitter feud between Munce and Geckles threatens to tear them apart, just when unity is needed most…when they are about to confront the Skull Sorcerer and Grief-Bringer!

added.title: The Ascent
added.description: Cole, the Lowly, Princess Vania and Wu discover that the stone-mech is fueled by Elemental Power, and attach it to the mine-carts in an effort to blast their way out of the mountain to confront the evil Skull Sorcerer!

added.title: Head Chef
added.description: Mao Mao faces off with Badgerclops in a competition to determine whether cooking (and being a hero) is an art or a science.

added.title: Sugar Berry Fever
added.description: Mao Mao tries to hide his love of cobbler.

added.title: Why So Blue?
added.description: Steven has heard rumors of a pair of Gems that are still destroying worlds. If he can't stop them, maybe Lapis can.

added.title: Little Graduation
added.description: Steven and the Gems celebrate Little Homeschool's first graduating class.

added.title: Countdown
added.description: Axel has to clean up the living room in time for his uncle's dinner party, but trying to do too much at once leaves him stuck as a toy with Orangutank on the loose and less than an hour until the guests arrive.

added.title: Joke's on You, Bro!
added.description: Axel and the team turn Galileo's camouflaging pranks around on him, convincing the gullible gecko that he's permanently invisible - to disastrous results!

added.title: Out of My Head
added.description: Axel must help Sarge and Bobbie learn to walk in each other's shoes - literally - after Luka unwittingly switches the toys' heads!

added.title: Freeze!
added.description: Axel and his team find themselves in a tough position after Ice Crusher makes it too cold for them to fight back at full speed.

added.title: King Axel
added.description: After a screening of the King Arthur tale, Axel holds out his sword and declares himself king, but when Dynamo uses his magnetism to steal the weapon and bestow it upon Masko, it casts doubt among the team over who is the true leader.

added.title: Fathers and Friends/Midsummer Nightmare
added.description: Midsummer Nightmare: Drago and the other AO Bakugan face an unseen threat with earth shattering power only to be left wondering if it was all a dream./Father's and Fiends: Osamu Kazami comes to take his son Shun back home and finds a defiance he hadn't counted on.

added.title: Dawn Before Dusk
added.description: Dawn Before Dusk, Part 1: The AO meet Benton Dusk discovering that their quiet little corner of the world is about to become much, much larger./Dawn Before Dusk, Part 2: Benton Dusk reveals that the AO have been indentified as persons of interest by powerful corporations including Philomena Dusk's AAAnimus.

added.title: Stratified/Maze Daze
added.description: Stratified: The AO embark on a mission into the mysterious labyrinth world of Vestroia to find Strata the Hunter and free the Bakugan he has imprisoned./Maze Daze: Lost in the maze of Vestroia the AO encounter powerful forces that seem to be struggling for control over the alien landscape.

added.title: All Jungled Up/Outer Demons
added.description: All Jungled Up: Still lost in Vestroia the AO experience mind altering effects of the nearby Core Cell and come face to face with the Bakuzon monster Tiko./Outer Demons: The AO find the doorway out of Vestroia only to learn they have entered a mirror world of their own imagining created by the Core Cell.

added.title: Matter of the Mind/Core Cell
added.description: Matter of Mind: Drago leads the Bakugan against the threat of Tiko to protect a powerful energy source called the Core Cell./Core Cell: The AO defend the Core Cell from an attack by Tiko and in a last ditch effort to save it Dan manages to evolve Drago into his L2 form.

added.title: Guardian of the Unikingdom
added.description: Hawkodile insists the Unikingdom is more dangerous than it looks and sets out to prove it by taking his friends on bodyguard patrol.

added.title: Cast Aside the Truth
added.description: Hawkodile breaks his arm in a careless spill and lies to his friends about the accident to keep from looking bad.

added.title: Unikitty and the Ice Pop Factory
added.description: An eccentric figure announces a contest to tour her marvelous ice pop factory, sending the gang on a frantic quest to find the winning popsicle stick.

added.title: Sunken Treasure
added.description: A relaxing beach day becomes an underwater adventure when Unikitty and her friends find a message in a bottle.

added.title: Dawn of the Donut
added.description: Dr. Fox's plans to deliver donuts all over the Unikingdom are sidetracked by Unikitty's reluctance to follow instructions.

added.title: Chip's Damage
added.description: Elodie enlists KO to help figure out what to do about Chip Damage.

added.title: The K.O. Trap
added.description: KO, Rad, and Enid are caught in an especially devious trap.

added.title: Whatever Happened to... Rippy Roo?
added.description: Rippy Roo visits the plaza.

added.title: Planet X
added.description: When Rad returns to his home planet, he learns a shocking truth about alien society.

added.title: Deep Space Vacation
added.description: When Gar lets KO and Enid take a vacation to outer  space, they get more than they bargained for.

added.title: Man Up
added.description: When Buttercup's aggression inadvertently allows villain Man-Boy to escape, she starts a new-age lifestyle in an effort to be more calm. But when Man-Boy returns to enact his revenge, Buttercup must embrace the balance between punching and hugging in order to defeat him.

added.title: Bye Bye, Bellum
added.description: The Mayor becomes dependent on the Powerpuff Girls after his assistant Ms. Bellum departs, leaving the girls so busy they accidentally hire the dangerous Bianca Bikini as his new assistant! When Bianca captures the Powerpuff Girls, the Mayor finds the tables turned and must rely on himself to help them.

added.title: Little Octi Lost
added.description: Buttercup steals Octi to teach Bubbles a lesson but ends up wanting to keep him for herself.

added.title: Strong Armed
added.description: When Bubbles breaks her arm and gets a powerful robotic cast, she must learn to stop being timid and embrace her smashy side to defeat the sleazy, sinister Pack Rat!

added.title: Power Up Puff
added.description: During a fight, both Buttercup and Bubbles are surprised to discover they've leveled up, leaving Blossom to wonder when or if she'll get new powers too.

added.title: A Change of Face
added.description: In Salem Massachusetts, Ben, Gwen and Max once again go up against Charmcaster, whose goal is to switch souls with Ben and possess the Omnitrix. However, Charmcaster first accidentally switches identities with Gwen, and then as spells fly back and forth, Ben and Gwen even end up in one another's bodies before they team up to get rid of Charmcaster once and for all.

added.title: Benwolf
added.description: In New Mexico, Max stops to visit an old friend, who's a Navajo Chief. Suddenly, a powerful storm comes out of nowhere. And behind bolts of purple lightning, a Navajo werewolf appears. As Ben battles the werewolf, he appears to be bitten and turns into Benwolf.

added.title: Monster Weather
added.description: Max takes the kids to a drought stricken Chicago to see his favorite golden oldie band perform at a huge music festival. Once there, our heroes cross paths with a deranged weatherman.

added.title: T.G.I.S
added.description: The Secret Saturdays come to Bellwood to investigate a rash of chupacabra attacks.

added.title: O Mother, Where Art Thou?
added.description: Ma Vreedle threatens to blow up the sun if Ben and the Plumbers don't find her missing son!

added.title: Mud Is Thicker Than Water
added.description: Ben, Gwen and Cousin Lucy try to find out how Psyphon's thugs are getting Plumber technology.

added.title: The Ultimate Heist
added.description: Albedo seeks a device that will finally change him back into his Galvan form; meanwhile, Ben is locked in Plumber HQ prison.

added.title: For a Few Brains More
added.description: Ben, Rook and Max must stop Ultimate Albedo from absorbing Azmuth's intelligence and taking over the galaxy.

added.title: Marcy & Hunson
added.description: Hunson Abadeer returns to Ooo to bond with his daughter Marceline, but will he be able to prove that he's changed his soul-sucking ways?

added.title: Blenanas
added.description: Finn's latest literary work is met with only derision so he sets out to prove all the naysayers wrong.

added.title: Temple of Mars
added.description: Searching for answers on Mars, Finn and Jermaine discover that they must first survive a cunning Martian mental trap.

added.title: Jake the Starchild
added.description: In order to fulfill his grand destiny, Jake is spirited away by a strangely familiar shape-shifting alien.

added.title: Gumbaldia
added.description: Finn and Jake, as ambassadors of the Candy Kingdom, travel to a powerful new city-state in a last ditch effort to stave off war.

added.title: K.I.L.I.T. Radio
added.description: Muscle Man wants a local radio station to play the song he wrote for Starla.

added.title: Carter and Briggs
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby enter a donut contest to win a cameo on their favorite cop show.

added.title: Skips' Stress
added.description: Skips has to lower his stress before it kills him.

added.title: Cool Cubed
added.description: The guys need to unfreeze Thomas' brain after he chugs a slushy.

added.title: Trailer Trashed
added.description: Muscle Man's trailer fails a health inspection and he wants to keep it at all costs.

added.title: Relaxation Land
added.description: Uncle Grandpa's relaxing weekend getaway quickly becomes a spooky nightmare for Pizza Steve.

added.title: Land of the Lost Shadows
added.description: When pieces of their shadows are stolen by a shadow demon, Uncle Grandpa and the gang must travel to the Land of Lost Shadows in order to retrieve them.

added.title: Pizza Eve
added.description: Uncle Grandpa falls for Pizza Steve's "girlfriend" and ends up in serious danger.

added.title: The Return of Aunt Grandma
added.description: Aunt Grandma is back and still bent on ruining Uncle Grandpa.

added.title: Messy Bessy
added.description: Seth must clean his room and learn to be a neater person in order to keep Messy Bessy from making his life a nightmare.

added.title: Parada de Descanso
added.description: Con el Rustbucket detenido en la carretera del Medio Oeste, Ben se encierra con su tablet mientras que Max y Gwen disfrutan del hermoso paisaje, hasta que el equipo Tennyson debe involucrarse en una persecución salvaje de un jackalope.

added.title: Es la cosa
added.description: Mientras visita un museo espacial, la emoción de Ben se multiplica cuando se entera de que están examinando en el laboratorio unas "cosas espaciales" que acaban de descubrir. Pero cuando esa cosa viscosa cobra vida y comienza a replicar a nuestro héroe con su capacidad de cambiar de forma, Ben debe buscar en su interior si quiere detener el caso de identidad equivocada.

added.title: El sentimiento
added.description: Mientras Max y Gwen se deleitan en el espíritu navideño de Winter Wonderland, Ben no podría estar más aburrido y concentrado en los juguetes. Pero cuando los Weatherheads fijan sus miras en Winter Wonderland como su próximo objetivo, nuestro héroe debe conectarse con sus emociones si quiere salvar la ciudad.

added.title: Alienigenas del Pasado, Presente
added.description: Cuando Ben encuentra un video en Internet en el que Cannonbolt destruye un laboratorio informático, el equipo Tennyson debe correr a State U para encontrar al impostor. Pero una vez que Ben descubra que una versión a vapor de su alienígena es la que está aterrorizando al campus, deberá derribar al hombre que está detrás de la máquina: iVapor Smythe!

added.title: Tiempo de Sonar
added.description: Después de una serie de pesadillas recurrentes que afectan su sueño, Ben se niega a contarles a Max y Gwen lo que le molesta. Pero una vez que se dan cuenta de que el propio Zombozo está detrás de las pesadillas, Ben debe aceptar la ayuda de Max y Gwen si quieren ponerle fin al terror.

added.title: El Ascenso
added.description: Cole, los de abajo, la princesa Vania y Wu salen de la montaña para enfrentarse al malvado Hechicero Calavera.

added.title: Los Maestros Nunca se Rinden
added.description: Cole, la princesa Vania, Wu y los humildes llegan a un templo, que una vez fue un campo de entrenamiento para los Maestros Elementales de la Tierra.

added.title: La Hora Mas Oscura
added.description: Los Ninjas, los Munces y los Geckles se refugian en la Cueva Fuerte Geckle , pero enfrentan al Hechicero Calavera y al Dragón Grief-Bringer.

added.title: El Dragon Grief-Bringer
added.description: Nya y Kai, quienes se han convertido en los líderes de los Munces y Geckles, intentan unirlos para derrotar a su enemigo mutuo, el Hechicero Calavera.

added.title: El Camino en el Calabozo
added.description: En su misión de derrotar al Rey Vangelis, Cole, Wu y Vania unen fuerzas con "Los de abajo" para encontrar una forma de salir del fondo de la montaña.

added.title: Fun Dungeon Face Off
added.description: Clarence's Mom treats Clarence, Jeff and Sumo to an afternoon at Rough Riders Chicken, a fast food restaurant with a play emporium. When Clarence and Sumo steal Jeff's fries, Jeff is forced to confront his germ phobias head-on in the restaurant's seemingly unsanitary play area.

added.title: Porque tan triste?
added.description: Steven ha escuchado rumores de un par de Gemas que todavía están destruyendo mundos. Si él no puede detenerlas, tal vez Lapis sí.

added.title: Pequena graduacion
added.description: Steven y las Gemas celebran la primera clase de graduados de la Escuela Madre.

added.title: Dollar Hunt
added.description: Clarence hosts a fun "dollar hunt" game to meet new friends. But things go awry when Clarence accidentally buries the money his Mom gave him to buy refreshments for her book club meeting.

added.title: Dream Boat
added.description: Sumo devotes himself to the Sisyphean task of building a boat, defying the expectations of everyone in his life, including himself.

added.title: #AbracadabraPalooza
added.description: En un intento por hacer que Karen se sienta mejor con un granito que le salió, Zee le cuenta la avergonzante transición que le dio poderes mágicos y la grieta que eso generó entre ella y su padre.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #GatoRabioso
added.description: Jessica Cruz está convencida de que puede conseguirle un hogar definitivo perfecto para Dexter, un gato que la gente considera inadoptable porque, básicamente, es el peor gato del mundo.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #LaBuenaLaMalaYLaBizarra
added.description: Las cosas van bien en la vida de Kara Danvers, como adolescente y como superheroína, hasta que comienza a hacerse responsable de cosas que no hizo y la aparición de un nuevo supervillano amenaza con destruir la reputación que tanto le costó ganar a Supergirl.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Pesadilla de Verano
added.description: Drago y los otros Bakugan de Los Fantásticos se enfrentan a una nueva y poderosa amenaza, solo para dejarlos preguntándose si todo habrá sido un sueño.

added.title: Padres y Amigos
added.description: Osamu Kazami viene para llevarse a su hijo Shun a casa y se encuentra con un obstáculo que no había contemplado.

added.title: Industrias Dusk Parte 1
added.description: Los Fantásticos conocen a Benton Dusk y descubren que su pequeño mundo está a punto de volverse mucho más grande.

added.title: Industrias Dusk Parte 2
added.description: Benton Dusk revela que Los Fantásticos son considerados personas de interés por poderosas corporaciones como AAAnimus.

added.title: Stratificados
added.description: Los Fantásticos emprenden una misión en el misterioso mundo laberíntico de Vestroia para buscar a Strata El Cazador y liberar a los Bakugan que tiene presos.

added.title: Aventura en el Laberinto
added.description: Perdidos en el laberinto de Vestroia, Los Fantásticos se enfrentan a poderosas fuerzas que parecen luchar por el control del planeta.

added.title: Atrapados en la Jungla
added.description: Aún perdidos en Vestroia, Los Fantásticos experimentan los efectos de la Célula Núcleo que altera sus cuerpos, y se encuentran cara a cara con el monstruo Bakugan, Tiko.

added.title: Demonios Internos
added.description: Los Fantásticos encuentran la forma de salir de Vestroia, pero descubren que en realidad están en un mundo paralelo.

added.title: Una Extrana Conexion
added.description: Drago lidera a los Bakugan contra la amenaza de Tiko, para proteger una poderosa fuente de energía.

added.title: La Celula Nucleo
added.description: Los Fantásticos defienden la Célula Núcleo de un ataque de Tiko, y en el último intento de Dan por salvarla, él y Drago logran liberar un nuevo poder.

added.title: Goose Chase
added.description: While at the park, Clarence happily feeds some birds his sandwich, imagining himself as their king. He has a great time until one persistent goose will not leave him alone!

added.title: Dust Buddies
added.description: As punishment for making a huge mess in their house, Belson's mom makes Belson clean up, offering their usual maid service to Mary and Clarence. Embarrassed of their messy house, Mary and Clarence hurry to clean up before the maid arrives.

added.title: Cuenta Regresiva
added.description: Axel tiene que limpiar la sala de estar a tiempo para la cena de su tío, pero tratar de hacer demasiado de una vez lo deja atrapado como un juguete con Orangutank suelto y menos de una hora hasta que lleguen los invitados.

added.title: Ahora Te Toca a Ti, Amigo
added.description: Axel y el equipo giran las bromas de camuflaje de Galileo sobre él, convenciendo al crédulo gecko de que es permanentemente invisible, ipara obtener resultados desastrosos!

added.title: Congelados
added.description: Axel y su equipo se encuentran en una posición difícil después de que Ice Crusher hace demasiado frío para que puedan defenderse a toda velocidad.

added.title: Rey Axel
added.description: Después de una proyección de la historia del Rey Arturo, Axel extiende su espada y se declara rey, pero cuando Dynamo usa su magnetismo para robar el arma y dársela a Masko, arroja dudas entre el equipo sobre quién es el verdadero líder.

added.title: El dia del hamster
added.description: Owen toma el trabajo de cuidar al hamster de la clase y descubre que es malvado.

added.title: Fuera de Mi Cabeza
added.description: iAxel debe ayudar a Sarge y Bobbie a aprender a caminar en los zapatos del otro, literalmente, después de que Luka involuntariamente cambia las cabezas de los juguetes!

added.title: La super moto
added.description: Duncan hace que Beth crea que rompió su bicicleta impulsada a batería y hace que lo lleve de un lugar a otro en su carrito todo el día como castigo.

added.title: Jefe de Cocina
added.description: Mao Mao se enfrenta a Colosal en una competencia para determinar si cocinar (y ser un héroe) es un arte o una ciencia.

added.title: Fiebre de la Baya de Azúcar
added.description: Mao Mao intenta ocultar su amor por el pastel de fruta.

added.title: Simon por siempre
added.description: Duncan y Leshawna tratan de aprovecharse del amor de Izzy por el juego de Simón Dice.

added.title: Through the Years: Finn the Human
added.description: Adventurer. Hero. Puncher of buns. Finn has come a long way from Boom Boom Mountain! Watch Finn grow up throughout 10 years of Adventure Time!

added.title: I Remember You Music Video
added.description: Bringing you another Adventure Time slow jam, it's Marceline and Ice King.

added.title: Through the Years: Princess Bubblegum
added.description: From a tiny gumball, to ruler of the Candy Kingdom, and now a great Warrior Princess! Not to mention those fun outfits! Check out the evolution of Princess Bubblegum throughout 10 years of Adventure Time!

added.title: Marceline Song Music Video
added.description: A song about Marceline written by Casey James Basichis.

added.title: Best LSP Freak Outs
added.description: OH. MY. GLOB. These are the best Lumpy Space Princess freak out moments. Which one is your favorite?

added.title: Simon and Marcy's Origin Story
added.description: 996 years ago, a man named Simon Petrikov met a little girl named Marceline at the end of the Great Mushroom War, and they became great friends.

added.title: Founder's Song Music Video
added.description: Dr. Gross sings a song about how the islands were started.

added.title: Best Finn and Jake Teamwork
added.description: Take a look at the most memorable Finn & Jake brotastic moments from Adventure Time. Which one is your favorite?

added.title: Food Chain Music Video
added.description: Finn teaches us about how the food chain works, through song.

added.title: Through the Years: Jake the Dog
added.description: Jake the Dog to Jake the Blue Alien... Winged... Dog? Whatever you call him now, there's no denying Jake is the master of shape-shifting, sage advice, and bacon pancakes! Watch Jake's transformation throughout 10 seasons of Adventure Time!

added.title: Craziest Characters
added.description: Lemongrab, Ricardio, the Clown Nurse. Which one is the all time craziest character on Adventure Time?

added.title: Slow Dance with You Music Video
added.description: Marceline performs a new song at her solo concert!

added.title: Dream of Love Music Video
added.description: Be prepared to be serenaded by the sweet, sweet sounds of Tree Trunks and Mr. Pig.

added.title: Frog Seasons, Spring (again)

added.title: Frog Seasons, Winter

added.title: Sow, Do You Like Them Apples

added.description: BMO wages war against a rat in the tree house, and Finn and Jake get sick.
